y Acker likewise work through many of the same problems of constructing texts in the wake of deconstruction, and so provide a glimpse of this post-deconstructive narrative approach to writing and interpretation at its most accomplished and powerful.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2024) 0aDeconstruction. 0aNarration (Rhetoric). 0aPostmodernism (Literature). 4aLiterature : American Literature. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Movements / Deconstruction.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013z978311148737340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780791487648?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780791487648423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780791487648/original  a978-3-11-148737-3  SUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles